    "Access the model in a way that does not leak data The first step when planning proprietary LLMs evaluation should be reading their most upto-date data policies, and access models accordingly (e.g.",
    "API instead of web interface for Ope-nAI's LLMs).",
    "We also acknowledge that in some cases this might not be viable due to budget limits, or an overly steep learning curve for the use of APIs by researchers outside of computer science.",
    "21 Interpret performance with caution The lack of system specifications and training details can make proprietary LLMs look like incredibly powerful tools with impressive zero-shot performance.",
    "This can often be explained by data contamination (Aiyappa et al., 2023)."
